noise floor: read from SX1302 spectral scan, fall back to packet-derived

Side-by-side test against a Waveshare SX1262 HAT-based monitor on the
same channel showed the dashboard reporting -78 dBm next to the HAT's
-120 dBm — a 42 dB gap.

Cause: we estimated the noise floor from per-packet rssi - snr, which
is mathematically an upper bound on the actual floor (loose for strong
neighbours, tight for weak ones). In a rural setup with one strong
neighbour and no weak traffic, the bound never tightens.

Fix: use the SX1302's built-in spectral scan API. Every 60s the chip
samples ambient channel power directly across 35 RSSI bins; we report
the 10th-percentile bin as the noise floor. Tuned to the same
frequency / bandwidth the radio is on, so the reading corresponds to
where Meshtastic packets actually land (not the 8 multi-SF auxiliary
channels at 125 kHz).

New files:
  src/hal/sx1302_spectral_scan.py    start/poll/read cycle + histogram
  src/hal/sx1302_signatures.py       extracted from wrapper for size budget
  src/api/telemetry/spectral_scan_service.py   60s asyncio scheduler
  tests/test_spectral_scan_result.py            histogram parsing tests
  tests/test_spectral_scan_service.py           service lifecycle tests
  docs/plans/v0.7.4-tests/spectral_scan.md      hardware test checklist

Modified:
  src/hal/sx1302_wrapper.py    expose run_spectral_scan(),
                               spectral_scan_supported (under 500 lines
                               via signatures extraction)
  src/api/telemetry/noise_floor.py
                               two-source: spectral primary, packet
                               rolling-min fallback. snapshot frame
                               gains a 'source' field
  src/api/server.py            wire SpectralScanService into lifespan
  src/config.py                add radio.spectral_scan_interval_seconds
                               (default 60, min 5, set 0 to disable)
  frontend/sidebar/telemetry_rail.{js,css}
                               source-aware tooltip; drop the
                               green/amber/red threshold coloring
                               (theater on packet-derived data,
                               unnecessary now that the number is real)

Tradeoff: each scan briefly pauses RX for ~50 ms. At 60s cadence
that is 0.08% downtime, well below normal RF packet-loss variance.
Minimum cadence clamped to 5s. Set the config to 0 to disable.

HAL fallback: spectral scan symbols are checked at load time. If the
loaded libloragw doesn't expose them (older builds), the service logs
a warning and the packet-derived path stays in use.

Tests: 11 new tests; full suite 648 passed, 3 skipped, ruff clean
on touched files. Hardware validation pending on .141.
